@NODE "Rules" "Rules"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Rules@{ub}
 ~~~~~
 In the start both players have two pieces each in the middle of the
 board. First Player1 puts a piece then Player2 and so on. When a player
 puts one of his pieces in the same line as one of his own with the other
 player's pieces between, all pieces will be changed to his colour.
 The lines can be horizontally, vertically or diagonally.
 One player can take pieces in several lines in different directions at
 the same time.

 The game ends when nobody can put a piece. The player who got the most
 pieces of his own colour at the end wins.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Description" "Window descripition"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Window description@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 In the top-right corner is the two player's name, rating and time.
 A raster indicating the player's color is beneath the player's stats.

 Under the two player's stats is four boxes. The upper two of the boxes
 is for player one the lower for player two. The left of the boxes means
 wins and the rightmost is the current number of pieces the player has.

 To the right of the score is a piece showing who's turn it is.

 Under the score and the turn piece is two symbols.
 An eye meaning about, and a trashcan symbolizing new or resign.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Menus" "Menus"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Menus@{ub}
 ~~~~~
 @{b}The project menu@{ub}
  New                    - End the current game and start a new.
  Open                   - Open a previously saved game.
  Save                   - Save the current game
  About                  - Test it!
  Quit                   - Quits the game

 @{b}The game menu@{ub}
  Single                 - Start a single game
  League                 - Start a league game
  Tournament             - Start a tournament game
  Statistics             - Bring up the statistics window

 @{b}The prefs menu@{ub}
  Customscreen           - Open up an own screen for GSReversi
  CloneWB                - Copy WB:s colors and pens (only for Standard)
  Rotate                 - Rotate all pieces when taken.
  FastComputer           - Skip delays for computer.

  Standard               - Turn on the standard piece set
  Marble                 - Use the marble piece set (MagicWB)
  Wooden                 - Use the wooden piece set
  Ice                    - Use the ice piece set (AGA)

 @{b}The hints menu@{ub}
  Show "best" move       - Shows the active player's best move

  Show possible moves    - Shows the active player's possible moves
  Show computer thinking - Shows how the computer value his possible moves

@ENDNODE

@NODE "NewGame" "How To Start a New Game"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}How To Start a New Game@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 The are three different ways to play GSReversi, @{"Single" LINK "GameTypes"}, @{"League" LINK "GameTypes"},
 @{"Tournament" LINK "GameTypes"}. To enter a player's name just click in one of the boxes
 and enter a name. If you want computer or a rated player click the right
 mouse buttton at the box where you want the computer or the player. A new
 box will appear, the @{"Player setup" LINK "Player"} dialog.
 See @{"Time" LINK "Time"} for the time configuration.
 Click "Play" to start a new game, and "Cancel" to don't start a new game.

 @{b}See Also@{ub}

 @{"New and resign" LINK "NewResign"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "GameTypes" "Game Types"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Single Game:@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~
 In a Single game two players play against each other. The game can be
 played in one, three or five rounds. If you choose "Best of One" the
 game won't end.
 
 @{b}League Game:@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~
 A League Game is a game with 2 to 8 players where everbody meets everbody
 in one to three rounds. The player who gets most points wins.


 @{b}Tournament Game:@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 In a tournament the player who gets most points in 1-3 games continues to
 next game and the other player is out of the tournament.
 A tournament needs 2, 4 or 8 players.

 A gain is worth 2 points, a draw 1 point and a loss 0 points.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Time" "Time Setup"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Time Setup@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~
 There are three different kinds of 'None', 'Move', 'Game'.
 If you have chosen @{b}Move@{ub} each player will get the time before each move.
 When choosing @{b}Game@{ub} the time will countdown from the first move.
 If any player runs out of time he has lost the game.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Player" "Player Setup"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Player Setup@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~
 In the Player Setup, Players and Computers are chosen. Every Player in
 the Player Setup has a rating, a number telling the level of the player.
 When a new player is created the rating is 1000. When the player plays
 against another rated player or computer, the ratings is increased if he
 wins - decreased if he loses.
 If a high-rated player wins against a low-rated player he gets few points.
 But if he has less rating than his opponent he gets plenty of points.

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Statistics" "Statistics"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Statistics@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~
 The statistics window appears by choosing Statistics in the Game menu.
 The players are sorted by rating in the listview gadget.

 Rat = Rating
 Pl  = Played
 W   = Wins
 D   = Draws
 L   = Losses

@ENDNODE

@NODE "NewResign" "New and Resign"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}New / Resign@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~
 If you click on the trashcan in the middle of a game, it means that you
 want to resign. If pressed before one of the player has made a move, it
 means that you want to abort the game and start a new one.

 If you plays a Single game with "best of one", new doesn't reset the score.

 You can always choose "New" in the project menu.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "OpenGame" "Open a Saved Game"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}How To Open a Saved Game@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 If you want to open a game you have saved before you just choose Open
 in the File menu.

 P.S. This option isn't available in the shareware edition. D.S.

 @{b}See Also@{ub}

 @{"Save a Game" LINK "SaveGame"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SaveGame" "Save a Game"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}How To Save a Game@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 When you are in the middle of a game and want to save it, you choose
 Save in the File menu. And when you want to continue the
 saved game you can open it with Open in the same menu.


 @{b}See Also@{ub}

 @{"Open a Saved Game" LINK "OpenGame"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Background" "Changing background"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}How To Change the Background@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 There are four different piece sets available, Standard, Marble,
 Wooden and Ice. The standard set can be shown in different screenmodes,
 HIRES, LACE and SUPERHIRES(ECS) with combinations. You can also choose
 SMALL for HIRES-LACE and SUPERHIRES-LACE.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "CustomScreen" "WB / CustomScreen"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}WBScreen / CustomScreen@{ub}
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 The standard set can always be on the WBScreen and the other sets, if the colors and the
 screenmode matches. To toggle between WBScreen and Customscreen use the CustomScreen item
 in the Prefs menu.

@ENDNODE

